**Changes since previous release**
- Based on SQLite version {SQLITE_VERSION}

> [!IMPORTANT]
> :pushpin: The _amalgamation source package_ including `configure` is _still_ **experimental**. :pushpin:
> Currently, only POSIX compliant systems are supported. Support files for building on Windows are included, but will only be adapted if the need arises.
Please report any issue you may experience using the [GitHub issue tracker](https://github.com/utelle/SQLite3MultipleCiphers/issues).
❗ Please share your experiences with this source package. TIA. ❗ 

**Notes**
This release contains the following precompiled binaries:
- SQLite3 binaries for Windows (SQLite3 shell and DLLs) _with_ resp. _without_ enabled ICU support in variants for 32-bit and 64-bit Windows. The SQLite3 shell applications support the [SQLite Archive](https://www.sqlite.org/sqlar.html) feature,
- Source code amalgamation (_amalgamation_) - a single C source file and a single C header file,
- Source code amalgamation (_autoconf_) - a single C source file and a single C header file - including a `configure` script for POSIX compliant systems,
- Precompiled SQLite Android library (see [SQLite Android Bindings](https://www.sqlite.org/android/doc/trunk/www/index.wiki)),
- Precompiled bundle of `sqlite3.wasm` and its JavaScript APIs, ready for use in web applications (see [SQLite3 WebAssembly](https://sqlite.org/wasm/)).